File: A general view of the headquarters of Eskom. AFP/Gianluigi Guercia JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says load-shedding will be reduced from Stage 2 to Stage 1 from 5am Wednesday. Stage 1 power cuts will now continue until 5am on Saturday. While Eskom has been able to return four generating units to operation, the generation system remains constrained. READ: Eskom CEO: SA to experience load-shedding for next 5 years Eskom CEO, Andre de Ruyter said this week, South Africa can expect more load-shedding over the next five years. He says the power utility will have a shortfall in electricity supply and that old power stations are the main reason for the blackouts. #POWERALERT1
Loadshedding will be reduced to Stage 1 from 05:00 on Wednesday and continue until 05:00 on Saturday as the power system is still severely constrained pic.twitter.com/V0LSjqKHDd